article.description: Snyder leads SE Missouri past Austin Peay 42-7
article.headline: Snyder leads SE Missouri past Austin Peay 42-7
article.linkText: Snyder leads SE Missouri past Austin Peay 42-7
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Kyle Snyder passed for 334 yards and five touchdowns, both career highs, to lead Southeast Missouri State to a 42-7 win over Austin Peay on Saturday. DeMichael Jackson rushed for 122 yards, moving up to fifth on the single season list (1,099) for the Redhawks (5-6, 3-4 Ohio Valley) and moved into the top 10 for his career (1,659). He had a receiving and rushing touchdown. Snyder also moved into fourth for single season yards at 2,377. The Governors (1-10, 1-6) were held to 284 yards and had three turnovers. They fell behind 28-0 before Damien Whitfield returned an interception 12 yards for a score early in the third quarter. Snyder had scoring passes of 71 yards to Spencer Davis, 70 and 15 yards to Paul McRoberts and 13 yards to Adrian Davis. Jackson's TDs were an 11-yard reception and 2-yard run.
